b'Wow, this community really showed up to raise awareness for ALL people living with diabetes, no matter their type or location. Together, we have #StrengthInNumbers:green_heart:

b'@mylifewithmody was diagnosed with diabetes when her dad wanted to check if his own blood glucose meter was working correctly and decided to randomly check her glucose. Well, her blood glucose was in the 300s! She was eventually diagnosed with MODY (Maturity-onset diabetes of the young), a genetic form of diabetes caused by a gene mutation, just like her dad.
.
Kylie is passionate about raising awareness about diabetes\xe2\x80\x94whether it\xe2\x80\x99s type 1, type 2, or MODY. And, we agree. No matter what type of diabetes you have, there is #StrengthInNumbers:green_heart:.
.
Help fill Instagram with green circles this #NDAM to show everyone how big this community is! Just add a green circle to your posts or stories, use #StrengthInNumbers:green_heart:, and share a few words of encouragement.
.

b'Happy Veterans Day, Warriors! :United_States: As we thank all of the brave women and men who have served in the armed forces, today we shine a light on #DexcomWarrior Cherise S. After completing her service in the Army Reserve, @sweetercherise was diagnosed with Latent Autoimmune Diabetes of Adulthood (LADA).
.
As chance would have it, her husband was diagnosed with #T2D on her 10th dia-versary! He served 24 years in the Army and is also using the #DexcomCGM system. 
.
Cherise loves connecting people with diabetes together online and credits the diabetes community as a great tool in her diabetes care -- introduce yourselves below and say hello! :waving_hand: 
.

b'Life for #DexcomWarrior Darla M. has changed drastically with Dexcom G6 and @myomnipod! Without them, her day was filled with fingersticks*, shots, managing highs and lows and constantly being on a strict schedule of eating.
.
\xe2\x80\x9cI love that both the Dexcom and the Omnipod are water-resistant** and are small enough to tuck away. The ability to see levels continually and being able to change #Omnipod settings helps control my levels better and keep from experiencing highs and lows.\xe2\x80\x9d
.
Being a busy first-grade teacher, #Dexcom and Omnipod have given Darla the freedom that she felt like she lost the day she was diagnosed.\xc2\xa0
.
Visit our website and @myomnipod to read more user stories and learn more about trial programs!
.
*If your glucose alerts and readings from the G6 do not match symptoms or expectations, use a blood glucose meter to make diabetes treatment decisions.
**The Dexcom G6 sensor and transmitter are water-resistant and may be submerged under eight feet of water for up to 24 hours without failure when properly installed. The receiver is not waterproof nor water-resistant.
.
#WarriorUp #diabetes #podder #t1d #t2d #teacher #diabetesmanagement'

b'Meet #DexcomWarrior @markjjr, former zookeeper who is now a wildlife biologist! :eagle: As a zookeeper, the Dexcom #CGM system helped Mark better manage his diabetes since his day was dictated by the animals. His activity levels changed based on how much there was to clean up or any type of training in the various exhibits.
.
Mark told us, \xe2\x80\x9cMy favorite Dexcom feature is probably the Dexcom CLARITY app reports. I love that I can share the code with my Endo (especially during #COVID19 times with virtual visits). I like the pop up alerts that tell me my percent in range. I think it\xe2\x80\x99s a great way to visualize control from day to day. For example, if I was 70% in range 1 day and 80% in range the next, it\xe2\x80\x99s easier to figure out what was different about the whole day rather than just looking at numbers.\xe2\x80\x9d
.
How have virtual visits helped you and your endocrinologist improve diabetes management this year?
.
#diabetes #dexcomg6 #t1dlookslikeme #type1diabetes #zookeeper #dexcom #diabetesawareness #diabeteslife #diabetescommunity #t1diabetes'
